The paper is primarily focused on distributed computing, which falls under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the expressibility of modal logic, which suggests a connection to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of algorithms and computational models, which could potentially place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.PL (Programming Languages). Finally, the paper discusses the containment relations between different classes of distributed computing models, which could be relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
